{
  "text": "In this study, we successfully applied the powerful approach established by Song et al. [CITATION_1] to select novel tissue-specific genes in the mouse. Among the 31 tissue-specific genes selected by microarray data analysis and semi-quantitative PCR analysis, there are 3 main categories: i) genes that were reported by previous publications to be secretory genes in the tissues in which we detected high expression; ii) genes that were reported by previous publications to be secretory genes, but secretion had not been reported in the tissues in which we detected high expression; and iii) genes that were not previously reported to be secretory genes.",
